namespace Pscf {
namespace Rp {

/*! 
\page rp_BoxLengthDerivative_page BoxLengthDerivative

This analyzer calculates the derivative of free energy with respect 
to the unit cell size of a cubic unit cell. 

\see BoxLengthDerivative (class API)

\section rp_BoxLengthDerivative_algorithm_sec Mathematical Formula

To be added

\section rp_BoxLengthDerivative_parameter_sec Parameter File

The full parameter file format, including all optional parameters, 
is shown below:
\code
BoxLengthDerivative{
  interval           int
  outputFileName     string
  hasAverage*        bool    (default true)
  nSamplePerOutput*  int     (default 1)
}
\endcode
Meanings of the parameters are described briefly below:
<table>
  <tr>
    <td> <b> Label </b>  </td>
    <td> <b> Description </b>  </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td> interval </td>
    <td> number of steps between data samples </td>
  </tr>
    <tr>
     <td> outputFileName </td>
     <td> name of output file </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
     <td>hasAverage</td>
     <td>whether the average and error analysis are needed?</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
     <td>nSamplePerOutput</td>
     <td>Number of sampled values per block average, and per output</td>
  </tr>
</table>

\section rp_BoxLengthDerivative_output_sec Output
Values of the derivative \f$  \frac{\partial F}{\partial L}  \f$ are
computed every interval simulation steps. 

By default, block averages of nSamplerPerOutput sequential sampled 
values are output every interval*nSamplerPerOutput time steps.

In the special case in which a ramp is enabled and 
nSamplePerOutput == 1, then \f$ L \f$ and a corresponding sampled 
value of \f$  \frac{\partial F}{\partial L}  \f$ are output to the 
file {outputFileName} every interval simulation steps.

If hasAverage is true, then at the end of the simulation:
  - average info and error analysis are output to {outputFileName}.ave
  - error analysis info are output to {outputFileName}.aer

*/

}
}
